Jill M. BUTLER, Plaintiff—Appellant, v. STATE FARM MUTUAL AUTO INSURANCE COMPANY, an Illinois corporation; Standard Insurance Company, an Oregon corporation, Defendants—Appellees. No. 02-35050. D.C. No. CV-00-00561-AJB. United States Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Argued and Submitted Oct. 8, 2002. Decided Oct. 15, 2002.

Before FERGUSON, FISHER, and TALLMAN, Circuit Judges.

MEMORANDUM *

Having reviewed the additional authorities cited by the appellant, including Black v. Arizala, 182 Or.App. 16, 48 P.3d 843 (2002), we AFFIRM for the reasons stated in the district court opinion.

AFFIRMED.

This disposition is not appropriate for publication and may not be cited to or by the courts of this Circuit except as provided by Ninth Circuit Rule 36-3.
